Fahrenheit 451 is a 1966 British Dystopian science fiction drama film directed by Fran√ßois Truffaut and starring Oskar Werner , Julie Christie , and Cyril Cusack .
Based on the 1953 novel of the same name by Ray Bradbury , the film takes place in a controlled society in an oppressive future in which a fireman , whose duty it is to burn all literature , becomes a fugitive for reading .
This was Truffaut 's first colour film as well as his only English-language film .
At the 1966 Venice Film Festival , Fahrenheit 451 was nominated for the Golden Lion .